# Support.io - UX/UI Tasks

## 🎨 Branding & Identity
- [x] Implement new color scheme: Primary Blue (#2563EB), Secondary Gray (#6B7280), Accent Green (#10B981).
- [x] Update typography to Inter or Roboto.
- [x] Update logo to the new design.

## 🖥️ General UX Guidelines
- [x] Implement clean and intuitive navigation.
- [x] Implement consistent dark/light mode support.
- [x] Create a dashboard-like homepage with access to all main tools.
- [x] Use clear iconography for DNS Check, SSL Check, Load Tester, etc.
- [x] Ensure mobile responsiveness.

## 📑 Homepage
- [ ] Add a brief introduction of Support.io as a technical support portal.
- [x] Implement a grid-based layout with cards for each tool (Load Tester, DNS Check, SSL Check).
- [ ] Add a "Start Testing Now" CTA button.

## ⚙️ Tool Pages
- [ ] Implement simple input forms with inline feedback validation.
- [ ] Visualize Load Tester results with charts (status codes, response times).
- [ ] Visualize DNS Check results in a table view with DNS records.
- [ ] Visualize SSL Check results with certificate details and expiration alerts.

## 🌙 Dark Mode
- [ ] Implement a dark theme with a contrast ratio > 4.5 (WCAG compliant).
- [ ] Implement a smooth toggle between light and dark mode.

## 📱 Responsiveness
- [x] Optimize for desktop, tablet, and mobile.
- [ ] Use cards and accordion components for smaller screens.

## 🔒 Accessibility
- [ ] Add ARIA labels for forms and buttons.
- [ ] Ensure keyboard navigability.
- [ ] Implement proper focus states for all inputs and actions.

## 🚀 Performance
- [ ] Use lightweight UI components.
- [ ] Implement lazy loading for heavy charts/data.
- [ ] Ensure a fast feedback loop after requests.
